573
00:53:39,480 --> 00:53:43,393
Give me a little more.
Don't be shy. Come on.

574
00:53:49,560 --> 00:53:52,597
Yeah. Oh, trouble at the trough.

575
00:53:52,760 --> 00:53:54,876
It's gonna get ugly.

576
00:53:58,440 --> 00:54:00,476
- What's eating Tor, huh?
- Not you.

577
00:54:00,680 --> 00:54:05,595
Yeah, I guess you're right.
War does some weird things to people.

578
00:54:28,720 --> 00:54:30,438
Everything okay?

579
00:54:36,800 --> 00:54:39,837
No, I'm... Yeah, I'm fine.

580
00:54:57,360 --> 00:55:02,195
- You look a little shaky, trooper.
- Yeah, something's not right.

581
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:05,318
That's what they call it
when you're behind enemy lines.

582
00:55:05,480 --> 00:55:07,311
It feels worse than that.

583
00:55:07,480 --> 00:55:10,313
Oh, is this another one
of your psychic hot flashes?

584
00:55:10,480 --> 00:55:12,357
It seems like Tor has changed.

585
00:55:12,520 --> 00:55:15,193
Because he wouldn't take
Brick's bait? About time.

586
00:55:15,360 --> 00:55:18,830
- It seems sudden, sarge.
- Like you puking your guts out?

587
00:55:19,000 --> 00:55:21,514
I guess I'm coming down
with something.

588
00:55:21,680 --> 00:55:24,399
- I wonder what that could be?
- There's a big knot...

589
00:55:24,560 --> 00:55:26,152
...where my stomach used to be.

590
00:55:26,320 --> 00:55:30,029
Sarge, I barely touched the medic's
hand just now, and I saw something.

591
00:55:30,200 --> 00:55:33,033
- You saw something?
- Something terrible.

592
00:55:33,560 --> 00:55:37,439
- Maybe you're just going crazy.
- I love you too, sarge.

593
00:55:38,840 --> 00:55:40,796
Girls get wacky
when they're pregnant.

594
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:44,231
Suddenly, they know everything
about everything.

595
00:55:45,800 --> 00:55:47,119
Oh, Jesus.

596
00:55:48,800 --> 00:55:52,156
Yeah, you're about as psychic
as a doorknob, trooper.

597
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:26,517
You ready?

598
00:56:26,680 --> 00:56:31,549
I'm kind of tired.

599
00:56:33,880 --> 00:56:37,555
- I'll give you a hand.
- Oh, thanks.

600
00:56:37,720 --> 00:56:40,075
Oh, my shoe.

601
00:56:40,240 --> 00:56:42,390
Don't worry about it.

602
00:56:46,880 --> 00:56:50,668
- Are you scared to shower, Otter?
- What does it matter?

603
00:56:50,880 --> 00:56:53,553
We're going home
in a few hours anyway.

604
00:57:10,200 --> 00:57:11,553
Hi, guys.

605
00:57:17,800 --> 00:57:19,438
Holy God, what the...?

606
00:57:43,720 --> 00:57:46,154
Oh, God. Oh, God.

607
00:57:57,040 --> 00:58:00,589
Open the door! Open the door!
We're gonna die in here!

608
00:58:00,760 --> 00:58:02,910
Open the door!

609
00:58:31,560 --> 00:58:35,917
Captain, I need to talk to you,
but it's gonna sound crazy.

610
00:58:36,120 --> 00:58:38,315
- Well, spit it out, trooper.
- Look, sir...

611
00:58:38,480 --> 00:58:41,153
...I know I'm not really
supposed to be psychic...

612
00:58:41,320 --> 00:58:43,276
...but I have this terrible feeling.

613
00:58:48,880 --> 00:58:51,713
- Yes, sir.
- As you were.

614
00:58:51,880 --> 00:58:56,954
We have a situation here that requires
the attention of Military Intelligence.

615
00:58:57,480 --> 00:58:59,948
- Tell him.
- This morning, in the mess...

616
00:59:00,120 --> 00:59:03,635
...I accidentally touched Griff's hand.
I might've had a vision.

617
00:59:04,200 --> 00:59:06,236
Playing psychic again, private?

618
00:59:06,400 --> 00:59:08,834
Could you keep
an open mind here, lieutenant?

619
00:59:09,000 --> 00:59:11,309
This trooper's
got information that's vital.

620
00:59:11,520 --> 00:59:14,956
Some of the troopers have been
acting a little strange lately.

621
00:59:18,800 --> 00:59:21,872
Describe what you saw.

622
00:59:22,040 --> 00:59:24,395
He wasn't a man.
He was some other thing.

623
00:59:24,560 --> 00:59:27,120
Maybe 1000 things.
Somehow he was connected...

624
00:59:27,280 --> 00:59:32,070
...to Tor and Sandee and Horton
and that new girl, Soda.

625
00:59:32,240 --> 00:59:36,995
I've always been pretty fuzzy, sir,
and this came through sharp as a knife.

626
00:59:38,400 --> 00:59:41,233
Lieutenant, I know I'm not
a real psychic like you.

627
00:59:41,400 --> 00:59:45,279
In fact, I just found out
I'm pregnant, and I didn't have a clue.

628
00:59:47,480 --> 00:59:50,711
- You're pregnant?
- Yes, sir, I'm afraid so.

629
00:59:50,920 --> 00:59:53,718
You might be interested to know
that in our studies...

630
00:59:53,880 --> 00:59:57,429
...pregnancy has been shown
to heighten psychic ability.

631
00:59:57,600 --> 01:00:00,637
That's too bad because
I'd really like to be wrong.

632
01:00:00,840 --> 01:00:06,312
Yes, me too, but I keep having
the same feeling.

633
01:00:06,480 --> 01:00:08,755
What is it?

634
01:00:08,920 --> 01:00:10,876
They're coming to wipe us out.

635
01:00:12,360 --> 01:00:13,713
What's so new about that?

636
01:00:14,160 --> 01:00:19,075
I mean the whole species, everything
human. And they have a plan.

637
01:00:20,080 --> 01:00:23,550
Look, after what I did in the battle...

638
01:00:23,720 --> 01:00:26,280
...I wasn't very sure
of myself anymore.

639
01:00:26,440 --> 01:00:30,353
And I just figured everybody
thought I'd just cracked.

640
01:00:34,400 --> 01:00:38,393
Yesterday, I might have been
inclined to agree...

641
01:00:38,600 --> 01:00:41,876
...but that would've been me
screwing up, lieutenant.

642
01:00:46,280 --> 01:00:48,396
Thank you, sir.

643
01:00:49,760 --> 01:00:54,834
I'll get on this matter
with General Shepherd immediately.

644
01:00:55,000 --> 01:00:57,992
Oh, and, trooper...

645
01:00:58,160 --> 01:01:00,196
...that was some good work.

646
01:01:00,360 --> 01:01:02,237
Sir.

647
01:01:31,520 --> 01:01:33,795
General Shepherd?

648
01:01:38,480 --> 01:01:40,835
What are you doing in here?

649
01:01:42,560 --> 01:01:45,518
General Jack and I
were just having a chat.

650
01:01:45,680 --> 01:01:47,830
What are you doing here, Dill?

651
01:01:48,000 --> 01:01:49,797
You and Shepherd?

652
01:01:53,520 --> 01:01:55,476
Is that so hard to believe?

653
01:01:58,600 --> 01:02:00,477
General?

654
01:02:00,640 --> 01:02:03,313
General Shepherd?

655
01:02:07,600 --> 01:02:09,397
General...

656
01:02:23,040 --> 01:02:27,397
They're inside of you. Oh, God.

657
01:02:30,480 --> 01:02:33,358
Back up, or I'll drill your damn skull.

658
01:02:33,560 --> 01:02:35,949
Get back! Get away from the door.

659
01:02:36,160 --> 01:02:37,639
Get away.

660
01:02:40,120 --> 01:02:43,669
You bastards. You're all under arrest...

661
01:02:43,840 --> 01:02:48,277
...for murder, sedition,
for treason against the Federation...

662
01:02:48,920 --> 01:02:52,117
Oh, and you're gonna pay
because we're not gonna kill you.

663
01:02:52,320 --> 01:02:56,313
Oh, no. No, you see, we got
special places for things like you...

664
01:02:56,480 --> 01:02:58,038
...where they cut you up.

665
01:02:58,200 --> 01:03:00,668
But they keep you alive
while they cut you up...

666
01:03:00,840 --> 01:03:05,630
...so they can see what makes you tick,
and they'll see what makes you sick.

667
01:03:05,840 --> 01:03:11,597
And I'll be there. Oh, yeah,
I'm gonna be there to see...

668
01:03:23,840 --> 01:03:26,434
You're under arrest, Dax.

669
01:03:26,600 --> 01:03:28,670
On what charge?

670
01:03:28,840 --> 01:03:30,558
Murder.

671
01:03:53,640 --> 01:03:58,111
- Captain Dax, what's happening?
- No talking to the prisoner.

672
01:04:07,360 --> 01:04:10,955
Keep him covered.
You gave me your word, Dax.

673
01:04:11,160 --> 01:04:14,994
What makes you think I had
anything to do with this, general?

674
01:04:22,080 --> 01:04:25,868
- Lock him up, sergeant.
- Yes, sir. With pleasure, sir.

675
01:04:34,040 --> 01:04:37,316
- Get out of here now, Sahara.
- Move it.

676
01:04:45,840 --> 01:04:47,910
You know what to do, Billie.

677
01:04:48,080 --> 01:04:50,116
Yes, sir.

678
01:05:02,080 --> 01:05:03,718
Why are you doing this, Billie?

679
01:05:03,920 --> 01:05:07,549
It's not you and me.
It's gonna happen to all of us.

680
01:05:18,160 --> 01:05:21,596
You trying to make a baby
with my barracks door, private?

681
01:05:26,120 --> 01:05:29,078
Sahara, she don't want it,
but I gotta give her the Bug.

682
01:05:29,240 --> 01:05:34,360
- There's a wire loose in your head.
- No, it's a little piece of God.

683
01:05:34,520 --> 01:05:38,399
Not like the one people used
to believe in, or the Federation...

684
01:05:39,120 --> 01:05:44,478
...and it's filling me up. I can sort
of feel myself floating away.

685
01:05:44,680 --> 01:05:47,478
Kid, you're not making any sense.

686
01:05:48,960 --> 01:05:51,758
You'll understand when you wake up.

687
01:05:51,920 --> 01:05:54,480
When I wake up?

688
01:06:00,360 --> 01:06:03,511
- Don't fight.
- That'll be the day.

689
01:06:16,120 --> 01:06:17,951
No!

690
01:06:56,160 --> 01:06:58,515
You Ionely, captain?

691
01:07:47,080 --> 01:07:49,833
Billie, please don't. Please.

692
01:11:32,720 --> 01:11:35,075
What the hell's going on, sergeant?

693
01:11:35,560 --> 01:11:38,677
- The Bugs are inside, sir.
- Inside the perimeter?

694
01:11:38,880 --> 01:11:40,472
No, sir.

695
01:11:41,960 --> 01:11:43,712
Inside me.

696
01:11:43,920 --> 01:11:46,275
Sergeant, no! No!

697
01:12:01,640 --> 01:12:03,153
Keys.

698
01:12:06,040 --> 01:12:08,315
- What the hell kind of Bug is that?
- Jesus.

699
01:12:08,880 --> 01:12:12,555
One that gets inside and takes over.
Maybe it can tell us something.

700
01:12:13,160 --> 01:12:14,991
What are you talking about?

701
01:12:32,920 --> 01:12:35,957
Everything that happened here
was supposed to happen.

702
01:12:36,160 --> 01:12:38,549
The Bugs brought us here
to create a weapon.

703
01:12:38,760 --> 01:12:41,593
- What kind of weapon?
- Shepherd!

704
01:12:42,240 --> 01:12:44,390
He could bring this
to the top of the Federation!

705
01:12:44,960 --> 01:12:46,393
We gotta kill the general.

706
01:13:06,160 --> 01:13:07,991
Fire in the hole!

707
01:13:13,160 --> 01:13:15,674
You're gonna die!

708
01:13:17,920 --> 01:13:19,956
They don't kill so easy, do they?

709
01:13:20,160 --> 01:13:22,549
- You're gonna die!
- They're not like us, sir.

710
01:13:22,760 --> 01:13:25,877
Not anymore. They're Bugs.

711
01:13:29,440 --> 01:13:33,672
You're gonna die!
You're gonna die!

712
01:13:35,520 --> 01:13:37,750
They shut down the reactors.

713
01:13:53,440 --> 01:13:54,714
Sandee?

714
01:13:56,320 --> 01:13:57,912
Grenade!

715
01:14:00,720 --> 01:14:02,631
Sahara, you okay?

716
01:14:10,080 --> 01:14:11,752
Poor creatures.

717
01:14:14,280 --> 01:14:16,714
Why must we destroy you?

718
01:14:16,880 --> 01:14:18,472
I'll tell you why.

719
01:14:19,920 --> 01:14:23,595
Order is the tide of creation...

720
01:14:24,120 --> 01:14:26,714
...but yours is a species...

721
01:14:27,040 --> 01:14:30,555
...that worships the one over the many.

722
01:14:31,120 --> 01:14:34,032
You glorify your intelligence...

723
01:14:34,200 --> 01:14:38,113
...because it allows you
to believe anything.

724
01:14:38,800 --> 01:14:41,030
That you have a destiny.

725
01:14:42,240 --> 01:14:44,310
That you have a right.

726
01:14:44,920 --> 01:14:47,150
That you have a cause.

727
01:14:47,640 --> 01:14:49,870
That you are special.

728
01:14:50,840 --> 01:14:52,831
That you are great.

729
01:14:53,040 --> 01:14:54,871
But in truth...

730
01:14:56,880 --> 01:14:59,838
...you are born insane.

731
01:15:01,720 --> 01:15:04,154
And such misery...

732
01:15:04,920 --> 01:15:07,354
...cannot be allowed...

733
01:15:08,360 --> 01:15:10,430
...to spread.

734
01:15:10,880 --> 01:15:12,393
Kill them all!

735
01:15:18,080 --> 01:15:20,548
Sahara! You get the general!

736
01:17:30,400 --> 01:17:33,039
- General Shepherd!
- That's me!

737
01:17:33,560 --> 01:17:36,677
You can't take him! Whatever you do,
don't let him onboard!

738
01:17:40,240 --> 01:17:42,196
Hey, general!

739
01:18:01,840 --> 01:18:04,229
Listen up. She needs medical attention.

740
01:18:04,400 --> 01:18:06,709
You just killed
a general officer, mister!

741
01:18:06,880 --> 01:18:09,314
Lots of generals out there, flyboy!

742
01:18:09,600 --> 01:18:13,275
This trooper's got information vital
to the survival of the Federation!

743
01:18:13,440 --> 01:18:16,398
She must reach safety at all costs!
You get me?

744
01:18:16,600 --> 01:18:18,113
Yes, sir!

745
01:18:21,280 --> 01:18:23,669
- Let's go!
- There are too many of them, Dax!

746
01:18:23,840 --> 01:18:27,594
You gotta tell them what you saw.
You gotta tell them about the new Bug!

747
01:18:27,800 --> 01:18:29,392
You stay here, you'll die!

748
01:18:29,600 --> 01:18:31,158
Murderers don't go home.

749
01:18:36,320 --> 01:18:37,594
Dax!

750
01:18:41,920 --> 01:18:43,990
Dax!

751
01:19:29,000 --> 01:19:32,629
Dax. More than a soldier,
not just a man.

752
01:19:32,840 --> 01:19:34,637
A hero of the Federation.

753
01:19:38,320 --> 01:19:41,153
He gave his life so we could fight...

754
01:19:41,360 --> 01:19:43,590
...and these words for us to live by:

755
01:19:43,760 --> 01:19:48,834
"Shed no tears for me.
My glory lives forever."

756
01:20:01,640 --> 01:20:03,949
And now you too can live the glory...

757
01:20:04,120 --> 01:20:07,874
...because it's easy to be a hero
in the Mobile Infantry.

758
01:20:08,040 --> 01:20:10,600
Men and women lik e you
are signing up every day...

759
01:20:10,760 --> 01:20:13,638
...to serve the Federation
and save the galaxy!

760
01:20:13,800 --> 01:20:15,711
Isn't it time you did your part?

761
01:20:15,880 --> 01:20:17,279
Beautiful baby, ma'am.

762
01:20:18,360 --> 01:20:19,634
Thank you, sergeant.

763
01:20:19,840 --> 01:20:22,400
Think how impressed friends
and teachers will be!

764
01:20:22,560 --> 01:20:23,834
Everyone loves a citizen!

765
01:20:24,000 --> 01:20:25,319
Little trooper likes me.

766
01:20:25,520 --> 01:20:28,080
Sign up, and one day
they'll call you a hero too!

767
01:20:28,240 --> 01:20:31,755
Hurry up, spud.
We need fresh meat for the grinder.

768
01:20:44,600 --> 01:20:49,390
Shed no tears for me.
My glory lives forever.

